P14 Project Specification
Automated Biomarker Discovery and Annotation for MPM via Literature Mining
________________________________________
1. Project Overview
Develop an automated NLP-based pipeline to extract, annotate, and curate MPM (Malignant Pleural Mesothelioma) biomarkers from biomedical literature, enabling systematic and continuously updatable biomarker discovery.
________________________________________
2. Objectives
•	Automatically retrieve MPM-related literature from PubMed
•	Identify biomarker entities using Named Entity Recognition (NER)
•	Extract biomarker-disease relationships via relation extraction
•	Build a structured, annotated biomarker database
•	Cross-validate findings against existing databases
________________________________________
3. Tech Stack
Module	Tools/Frameworks
Literature Retrieval	PubMed API (Entrez/Biopython)
NER Model	BioBERT / scispaCy
Relation Extraction	Rule-based + BioBERT RE
Data Storage	SQLite / MongoDB
Visualization	Streamlit (optional)
________________________________________
4. System Pipeline
PubMed Query
    ↓
Abstract / Full-text Retrieval
    ↓
NER (genes, proteins, biomarker entities)
    ↓
Relation Extraction (biomarker → diagnosis / prognosis / treatment)
    ↓
Cross-validation (against UniProt, MeSH, existing MPM databases)
    ↓
Structured Storage + Query Interface
________________________________________
5. Deliverables
•	✅ Automated literature retrieval script
•	✅ NER annotation module
•	✅ Relation extraction module
•	✅ Structured biomarker database (attributes: type, function, validation status)
•	✅ Simple query/search interface
________________________________________
6. Timeline (8 Weeks)
Week	Task
Week 1–2	Literature retrieval & data collection
Week 3–4	NER model fine-tuning & testing
Week 5–6	Relation extraction & cross-validation
Week 7	Database construction & population
Week 8	System testing & report writing
________________________________________
7. Evaluation Metrics
Metric	Description
Precision / Recall / F1	NER and relation extraction performance
Coverage Rate	Overlap with known databases (UniProt, MeSH)
Update Efficiency	Time cost for incremental literature updates
________________________________________
8. Expected Outcomes
•	A curated, searchable MPM biomarker database
•	Reproducible NLP pipeline adaptable to other cancer types
•	Foundation for integration into larger MPM molecular marker platforms (P13–P18)
